OK?

09:36.560 --> 09:38.560
It's Pete, isn't it?

09:39.920 --> 09:41.560
Yeah.

09:44.560 --> 09:47.760
OK, Adam's given each of you an extensive...

09:47.760 --> 09:50.560
- Mm-hm.
- ..rundown of your characters.

09:50.560 --> 09:54.560
So, let's explore the dynamic between him and his friends.

09:54.560 --> 09:56.600
- Adam?
- Yes?

09:56.600 --> 09:59.560
- Oh, I'm sorry, yeah.
- You lead off.

10:03.240 --> 10:06.560
Pete, me old mate.

10:06.560 --> 10:08.560
My old mucker.

10:08.560 --> 10:10.560
You know, Jenny's always had the hots for me.

10:10.560 --> 10:12.560
Has she?

10:12.560 --> 10:14.560
Oh, David.

10:14.560 --> 10:16.560
Lover boy always had a way with the girls.

10:16.560 --> 10:18.560
Whoa, whoa, whoa... What are you doing?

10:18.560 --> 10:20.560
Oh, you said Karen's sexy.

10:20.560 --> 10:22.560
- Yes.
- I'm being sexy.

10:22.560 --> 10:25.560
Perhaps if you were a little less...

10:25.560 --> 10:28.760
- Obvious.
- Let's get back on track.

10:31.760 --> 10:35.560
You know, Adam's always had a very high opinion of himself.

10:35.560 --> 10:38.760
Mm, to be fair, I did have a crush on him when I was at school.

10:40.560 --> 10:42.560
And there was that moment years later

10:42.560 --> 10:43.560
when you made a pass at him.

10:43.560 --> 10:45.560
That's right, you did.

10:45.560 --> 10:48.600
The truth is she's always carried a torch for me.

10:48.600 --> 10:51.560
In your dreams!

10:51.560 --> 10:53.560
We're just mates now.

10:53.560 --> 10:56.400
Well, no, Jen, deep down, you still have feelings for me.

10:56.400 --> 10:57.560
Why would you want her to?

10:57.560 --> 11:01.760
Because Adam needs to feel he can have any woman he turns his mind to.

11:01.760 --> 11:03.560
Not much of a friend, if it includes my wife.

11:05.560 --> 11:07.560
There is a vein of selfishness that runs through him.

11:07.560 --> 11:09.560
Not his most attractive quality.

11:09.560 --> 11:11.560
- And then there's his arrogance.
- Arrogance?!

11:11.560 --> 11:14.560
Yeah, the way you regard yourself as the lead singer

11:14.560 --> 11:16.560
and the rest of us as the backing vocals.

11:16.560 --> 11:18.600
- Like Boy George.
- And Culture Club.

11:26.560 --> 11:27.600
Erm...

11:30.760 --> 11:33.560
This helps me how, exactly?

11:50.560 --> 11:51.560
How was school?

11:55.560 --> 11:56.560
How's your meal?

11:59.400 --> 12:00.560
Matt, I cooked you your dinner.

12:00.560 --> 12:02.560
The least you could do is acknowledge that.

12:02.560 --> 12:04.240
Thank you, Father.

12:04.240 --> 12:06.600
This sauce is delicious. Did you microwave it yourself?

12:10.760 --> 12:12.560
Maybe irony is genetic.

12:14.560 --> 12:17.240
Matt, I've apologised about Gemma.

12:17.240 --> 12:18.560
I don't know what else I can do.

12:18.560 --> 12:21.560
Well, that's the problem right there, isn't it?

12:21.560 --> 12:22.560
Hm?

12:24.560 --> 12:27.240
My mates' dads make dad jokes.

12:27.240 --> 12:30.080
We laugh about them behind thier backs. They're embarrassing.

12:30.080 --> 12:31.560
But you're excruciating.

12:33.560 --> 12:35.600
You're so keen to be down with the kids.

12:35.600 --> 12:37.920
Don't you understand?

12:37.920 --> 12:39.560
I don't want you to be my friend.

12:39.560 --> 12:40.760
I want you to be my dad.

12:46.560 --> 12:47.560
OK.

12:50.560 --> 12:51.560
Thanks for dinner.

