16:13.600 --> 16:15.560
Listen! Oi!

16:15.560 --> 16:18.240
I might have cancer!

16:19.240 --> 16:21.600
I've been given three months to live.

16:28.560 --> 16:30.560
Well...

16:30.560 --> 16:31.600
fine.

16:32.560 --> 16:34.560
Hello.

16:36.560 --> 16:37.560
Yep, that's fine.

16:37.560 --> 16:40.560
- If you just take a seat over here for me.
- OK, thanks.

16:46.560 --> 16:48.560
Found somewhere to park, then?

16:49.560 --> 16:51.560
Ambulance bay.

16:53.560 --> 16:55.560
Sorry about before.

16:55.560 --> 16:57.560
Hey, it's a jungle out there.

16:57.560 --> 17:00.240
You do or say whatever you need to.

17:01.080 --> 17:02.560
Yeah.

17:08.560 --> 17:10.560
It's not true, is it?

17:10.560 --> 17:12.560
What you said about three months.

17:13.560 --> 17:15.560
Who knows?

17:15.560 --> 17:18.760
If I'm not here in three months, that's your answer.

17:30.560 --> 17:33.560
Olivia, do you know what Ellie's ordering online?

17:33.560 --> 17:35.560
Er, she's not, I don't think.

17:37.240 --> 17:39.560
You're covering for her is laudable.

17:39.560 --> 17:41.560
Slightly undermined by the evidence.

17:41.560 --> 17:45.560
- She's not buying stuff. They're gifts.
- For her birthday?

17:45.560 --> 17:46.560
Well, she's had a lot.

17:48.560 --> 17:50.560
She's rinsing men.

17:51.560 --> 17:53.560
I have no idea what that means.

17:53.560 --> 17:56.560
She makes friends with men on the internet and they send her gifts.

17:56.560 --> 17:58.560
What?!

18:03.920 --> 18:06.920
- I'm just using my initiative.
- No, you are prostituting yourself!

18:06.920 --> 18:09.560
Urgh, why won't you listen? It's got nothing to do with sex!

18:09.560 --> 18:11.560
I cannot believe you're being so stupid!

18:11.560 --> 18:13.560
No, I'm sorry. I mean naive.

18:13.560 --> 18:15.560
- We never meet.
- They know where you live!

18:15.560 --> 18:18.400
- We just talk over webcam.
- About what?

18:18.400 --> 18:20.600
Nothing! Movies I've seen. Music I like.

18:20.600 --> 18:22.600
- Why would they care?
- Thanks, Mum!

18:22.600 --> 18:24.560
No, what I mean is, what's in it for them?

18:24.560 --> 18:27.560
Friendship. They're just lonely, that's all.

18:27.560 --> 18:30.560
What, in exchange for that, they buy you gifts?

18:30.560 --> 18:32.560
I suggest stuff they might like to send me.

18:32.560 --> 18:34.560
You know, a pair of shoes, a necklace I've seen.

18:34.560 --> 18:36.560
Can you not see what's wrong with that?

18:36.560 --> 18:39.560
- They're bound to want more!
- Well, they're not going to get it.

18:39.560 --> 18:42.560
I don't know why you're having a go at me, you should be proud.

18:42.560 --> 18:44.560
- What?!
- Men have always used women.

18:44.560 --> 18:47.560
But now I'm the one in control. I'm not being exploited.

18:47.560 --> 18:50.560
No, they are! That's not feminism!

18:50.560 --> 18:53.560
That was your generation's struggle. We're way beyond all that.

18:53.560 --> 18:56.560
So, you use the freedoms that we won to get men to buy you stuff.

18:56.560 --> 18:58.560
- Designer labels.
- I want you to stop.

18:58.560 --> 19:02.560
Mum, it's fine. You just don't understand, that's all.

19:10.400 --> 19:13.560
You've had a busy day. A battery of tests.

19:13.560 --> 19:17.560
Too right. I feel like a toasted sarnie.

19:17.560 --> 19:19.560
There's a cafe near the entrance.

19:19.560 --> 19:22.560
Oh, no, I meant, you know, literally.

19:22.560 --> 19:24.560
Like I've been Brevilled.

19:25.560 --> 19:27.560
It's good you can see the funny side.

19:27.560 --> 19:29.560
You need a sense of humour.

19:35.560 --> 19:36.560
Do I, seriously?

19:38.560 --> 19:41.560
Some people prefer to wait till we have all the results.

19:41.560 --> 19:43.560
Well, good for them.

19:43.560 --> 19:46.560
But, I mean, if you know something already, then...

19:48.400 --> 19:50.560
..I want to, too, please.

19:52.560 --> 19:55.560
We'll need to see the outcome of your biopsy to be sure.

19:56.560 --> 19:59.560
But I have to say your test results are highly suspicious

19:59.560 --> 20:00.560
and indicative of cancer.

20:02.560 --> 20:03.560
OK.

20:06.560 --> 20:07.560
Thank you.

20:54.240 --> 20:55.560
Oh, God.

20:58.920 --> 21:00.560
Oh, shit.

21:09.560 --> 21:11.560
- Hello.
- Hey.

21:12.560 --> 21:14.560
- I didn't mean to intrude.
- No.

21:15.560 --> 21:17.560
It's, erm...

21:17.560 --> 21:18.560
It's fine.

21:19.560 --> 21:21.560
Sorry. Erm...

21:21.560 --> 21:22.560
Were you waiting for me?

21:23.560 --> 21:26.560
I just thought I'd check to see you're OK.

21:29.560 --> 21:31.560
Have you got a minute?

21:31.560 --> 21:32.560
Yeah.

21:33.560 --> 21:35.560
Till my parking runs out.

21:48.560 --> 21:51.560
So, you got the news that no-one wants.

21:54.560 --> 21:56.560
I knew it was a possibility or...

21:59.760 --> 22:01.920
It doesn't make it any less of a shock.

22:03.560 --> 22:04.760
No.

22:11.560 --> 22:13.400
You don't have to talk.

22:14.400 --> 22:16.560
We can just sit a while.

22:39.560 --> 22:41.560
You're in therapy?

22:41.560 --> 22:43.560
No. No, I'm doing drama therapy.

22:43.560 --> 22:45.760
- There's a difference.
- In what way?

22:45.760 --> 22:48.240
Well, for starters, I don't think it works.

22:48.240 --> 22:51.560
But it's good fun. It's a bit like am-dram, but it's all about you.

22:51.560 --> 22:54.560
Ah, yeah, I can see why you like it. No!

22:54.560 --> 22:56.560
It can be quite confronting.

22:56.560 --> 22:58.920
But people say very harsh things. You do.

22:58.920 --> 23:00.080
Me?

23:00.080 --> 23:03.240
Yeah, someone plays you and then we all improvise scenes together.

23:03.240 --> 23:04.560
- So, what's he likes?
- Who?

23:04.560 --> 23:06.240
- The bloke who plays Pete.
- Here you go.

23:06.240 --> 23:07.560
Oh, you know, erm...

23:07.560 --> 23:10.560
- You cheeky git. What, fat?
- No!

23:10.560 --> 23:11.760
- I've lost shed-loads!
- Not fat.

23:11.760 --> 23:13.560
Big-boned.

23:13.560 --> 23:15.560
- She's very nice, though.
- She?

23:15.560 --> 23:16.560
She?!

23:16.560 --> 23:19.560
- Oh, I'm not being played by a woman.
- That's a bit sexist, Pete.

23:19.560 --> 23:21.560
There aren't enough men. I'm played by a woman, too.

23:21.560 --> 23:23.560
- I bet she's not big-boned.
- Well, you know...

23:23.560 --> 23:25.560
I'll get this.

23:25.560 --> 23:27.560
- What? Have you come into money?
- After a fashion.

23:27.560 --> 23:28.760
Oh, hang on a minute.

23:28.760 --> 23:30.560
Isn't that...?

23:30.560 --> 23:33.560
That's Nikki. Yeah. It's a present.

23:33.560 --> 23:35.920
So you're constantly reminded of who's money you're spending?

23:35.920 --> 23:37.560
- Yeah, it cute, isn't it?
- Or controlling.

23:37.560 --> 23:39.560
You're a kept man.

23:39.560 --> 23:41.560
I prefer to see it as redressing the gender imbalance.

23:41.560 --> 23:44.560
David Marsden, the feminist.

23:44.560 --> 23:46.560
Well, one has to do one's bit.

23:53.560 --> 23:55.560
I'm watching you, David.

24:02.560 --> 24:05.560
So, erm...how are you getting on?

24:07.560 --> 24:09.560
I just can't see any hope.

24:11.560 --> 24:13.920
I don't know what there is to live for.

24:13.920 --> 24:17.400
Well, if you kill yourself, you'll never find out.

24:17.400 --> 24:18.760
Look, I once felt like you.

24:20.560 --> 24:23.560
I've sat where you are. And now I'm sat next to you.

24:23.560 --> 24:26.560
And one day, you'll be sat next to someone

24:26.560 --> 24:29.560
and you'll be telling them the same thing.

24:29.560 --> 24:31.560
It's going to be a crowded bench.

24:32.560 --> 24:34.560
Look, my point is, hang in there.

24:34.560 --> 24:36.560
Things'll get easier.

24:36.560 --> 24:38.560
You know, and once your medication takes effect...

24:38.560 --> 24:41.560
- You said that yesterday.
- It's 24 hours closer to kicking in.

24:41.560 --> 24:44.240
Oh, sorry.

24:46.560 --> 24:47.560
Adam?

24:47.560 --> 24:49.560
Where are you? We're meant to be there.

24:49.560 --> 24:51.560
Oh, shit! Sorry.

24:51.560 --> 24:52.560
Something's come up.

24:52.560 --> 24:55.560
Can you rearrange?

24:55.560 --> 24:57.560
- Dad, it's an audition.
- Look, I know. I know.

24:57.560 --> 24:59.560
- I'll call you in a minute.
- Oh, forget it.

24:59.560 --> 25:00.560
Adam?

25:00.560 --> 25:01.560
Adam!

25:01.560 --> 25:02.920
Oh...!

25:02.920 --> 25:04.560
Evan, wait!

25:04.560 --> 25:05.600
Evan!

25:08.560 --> 25:09.760
Oh!

25:11.080 --> 25:12.560
Rinsing?

25:12.560 --> 25:14.560
- I've never heard of it.
- I know.

25:14.560 --> 25:16.560
They think of new ways to torment you.

25:17.560 --> 25:19.560
I've got all this to come with our Chloe, I suppose.

25:19.560 --> 25:21.400
No, she's a great girl.

25:21.400 --> 25:23.560
Plus, she's got you and Pete.

25:25.560 --> 25:27.560
Oh, my God...

25:27.560 --> 25:28.560
What?

25:30.560 --> 25:31.560
Are you OK?

25:31.560 --> 25:33.560
Yes. Er, sorry.

25:33.560 --> 25:35.560
I... I am. Of course, yes. Miles away.

25:35.560 --> 25:37.080
Whoa!

25:37.080 --> 25:38.560
What's this?

25:38.560 --> 25:41.560
That is a manuscript that my business partner's asked me to read,

25:41.560 --> 25:43.560
written by a friend of his.

25:43.560 --> 25:45.560
Nina B St James. Never heard of her.

25:45.560 --> 25:48.560
No, and you never will. Even the title's crap.

25:48.560 --> 25:49.560
Love Comes Slowly.

25:49.560 --> 25:52.560
- Romance or porn?
- Chic lit.

25:52.560 --> 25:54.560
The sort of useless dross young women lap up

25:54.560 --> 25:56.560
when they could actually be thinking.

25:56.560 --> 25:58.560
- Not that I've read it.
- You are such a snob.

25:58.560 --> 26:01.560
- I know.
- Well, it sounds good.

26:01.560 --> 26:02.560
I'll read it.

26:02.560 --> 26:04.560
Good. Thanks.

26:04.560 --> 26:06.240
Tell me something nice I can say about it.

26:07.560 --> 26:08.760
I could do with the distraction, frankly.

26:10.560 --> 26:12.560
OK, who hasn't had a turn yet?

26:12.560 --> 26:15.560
Adam, would you like to perform another scene?

26:15.560 --> 26:17.560
I don't know. Is everyone just going to have a go at me?

26:17.560 --> 26:20.240
You mentioned the other day that you have a son.

26:20.240 --> 26:22.240
Matt. Yeah. He's, erm...17.

26:22.240 --> 26:23.560
He's a great kid.

26:23.560 --> 26:25.560
Karen, who you play, that's his godmother.

26:25.560 --> 26:27.920
We're not getting on very well at the minute.

26:27.920 --> 26:30.560
- You and Karen?
- No, Matt and I. Erm...

26:30.560 --> 26:33.400
He thought I was trying to get off with his girlfriend.

26:36.560 --> 26:39.400
- Maybe I should let someone else have a go.
- No.

26:39.400 --> 26:40.560
No.

26:40.560 --> 26:42.560
- Have you and Matt talked about this?
- Not much.

26:44.240 --> 26:45.560
He did shout at me.

26:45.560 --> 26:47.760
Why don't you try and explain yourself to him?

26:47.760 --> 26:50.560
Oh. Erm...

26:51.560 --> 26:53.560
Yeah, OK.

26:53.560 --> 26:55.560
OK. Who'll be Matt? Erica?

26:55.560 --> 26:58.560
- Can I be me?
- Yeah.

26:58.560 --> 27:00.760
Oh, shall I be Karen again?

27:00.760 --> 27:02.560
Erm, sure. Yeah, why not?

27:02.560 --> 27:03.760
Oh, er, maybe not so...

27:05.400 --> 27:06.560
..sexy this time.

27:06.560 --> 27:09.560
- I can't help it.
- No.

27:09.560 --> 27:12.400
OK, so, er, the scene is...

27:12.400 --> 27:13.560
..we're at home.

27:13.560 --> 27:15.560
Karen's turned up. I'm not sure why.

27:15.560 --> 27:18.400
And, erm, I'm talking to Matt.

27:19.760 --> 27:22.560
Why were you hitting on my girlfriend?

27:24.560 --> 27:26.240
Well, erm...

27:26.240 --> 27:27.560
..it was a misunderstanding.

27:27.560 --> 27:29.560
You know, I...I never knew that she was.

27:29.560 --> 27:31.560
And you think that makes it OK?

27:32.560 --> 27:33.600
He's right, Adam.

27:33.600 --> 27:36.560
What kind of sick individual tries to pull women

27:36.560 --> 27:38.560
- young enough to be his daughter?
- Well...

27:38.560 --> 27:40.560
..they're generally a wee bit older than that.

27:40.560 --> 27:42.560
This boy never knew his mother.

27:42.560 --> 27:46.560
Which means the example you set him is even more important.

27:51.560 --> 27:55.560
But...you think I'm failing as a father?

27:56.560 --> 27:59.560
You're not showing him how to have a long and lasting relationship.

27:59.560 --> 28:01.560
I can't.

28:01.560 --> 28:03.560
I've tried.

28:03.560 --> 28:04.560
Angela, Tina...

28:04.560 --> 28:06.560
But it never quite works.

28:06.560 --> 28:09.560
Is it because of my mum?

28:11.560 --> 28:13.560
She set the bar pretty high.

28:15.560 --> 28:16.920
I'd like to talk about her more.

28:16.920 --> 28:18.760
Would you?

28:18.760 --> 28:21.560
You said yourself, we don't much.

28:23.560 --> 28:26.560
I'm never sure you want to, so I don't bring her up.

28:26.560 --> 28:28.560
Which makes me think you don't want to.

28:28.560 --> 28:32.560
Oh, God, I'd love to make her real in your mind,

28:32.560 --> 28:34.560
but I never feel that my words will do her justice.

28:36.560 --> 28:38.240
Just hearing you talk like this

28:38.240 --> 28:40.400
makes me realise how special she was.

28:41.560 --> 28:42.560
Oh...

28:42.560 --> 28:44.560
She was.

28:45.920 --> 28:49.560
- Wasn't she?
- I never knew her, Adam.

28:51.240 --> 28:52.920
But I can well believe it.

28:55.560 --> 28:56.560
And so can I.

29:12.560 --> 29:14.560
I need to go.

29:19.560 --> 29:21.240
Matt?

29:23.560 --> 29:25.560
Can I show you something?

29:36.920 --> 29:39.240
Are you sure you want to watch this?

29:39.240 --> 29:40.560
I used to when I was a kid.

29:41.560 --> 29:43.240
I liked seeing it.

29:44.560 --> 29:46.240
Are you sure you do?

29:47.560 --> 29:48.560
Yeah.

29:52.560 --> 29:55.560
♪ Wake up, step up to reality...

30:04.560 --> 30:06.560
♪ In the morning when I wake

30:09.400 --> 30:11.760
♪ And the sun is coming through

30:13.920 --> 30:17.560
♪ Oh, you fill my lungs With sweetness

30:19.560 --> 30:22.560
♪ And you fill my head with you

30:24.560 --> 30:26.560
♪ Shall I write it in a letter?

30:29.240 --> 30:31.560
♪ Shall I try to get it down?

30:33.920 --> 30:37.560
♪ Oh, you fill my head with pieces

30:39.400 --> 30:41.560
♪ Of a song I can't get out

30:43.560 --> 30:46.600
♪ Can I be close to you? ♪

30:47.560 --> 30:49.560
I miss her.

30:51.240 --> 30:53.560
I miss the idea of her.

30:53.560 --> 30:56.560
♪ Can I be close to you?

30:56.560 --> 30:58.560
♪ Oooh

30:59.920 --> 31:02.240
♪ Oooh. ♪

31:03.560 --> 31:05.560
I'm going to stop seeing women half my age.

31:07.560 --> 31:08.600
You need a mum.

31:10.760 --> 31:12.560
Not a big sis or...

31:13.560 --> 31:16.240
..or an aunt you might fancy.

31:18.240 --> 31:19.560
And I need...

31:22.560 --> 31:25.560
..not someone who'll replace your mum.

31:25.560 --> 31:28.560
Someone to succeed her...maybe.

31:34.560 --> 31:36.560
But even that's not easy.

31:38.560 --> 31:40.560
I loved her so much. I mean, look at us.

31:45.560 --> 31:47.560
The thought of spending the rest of my life with someone else...

31:51.760 --> 31:53.560
..it still seems like...

31:55.560 --> 31:58.560
..deep down, a sort of a betrayal.

32:08.560 --> 32:10.560
I think Mum would just want you to be happy, Dad.

32:30.060 --> 32:31.740
Oh, Ian. Hi.

32:31.740 --> 32:34.060
You owe me an essay.

32:34.060 --> 32:36.060
Yeah, sorry about that.

32:36.060 --> 32:38.060
I need an extension.

32:38.060 --> 32:40.060
Actually, you know what, I might need to defer my place.

32:40.060 --> 32:43.060
Why? You're doing so well.

32:43.060 --> 32:47.060
Thanks. Yeah, I am... I'm loving it.

32:47.060 --> 32:50.060
It's just I've got stuff going on at home.

32:50.060 --> 32:53.060
- It makes it difficult to study.
- I see. Er...

32:53.060 --> 32:54.060
Would it help to talk about it?

32:54.060 --> 32:57.260
The university has a very good counselling service.

32:57.260 --> 33:01.060
Don't they mainly deal with sexually transmitted diseases?

33:01.060 --> 33:04.900
And students whose selfies aren't getting enough likes.

33:06.060 --> 33:09.060
I'd rather not say anything for the minute to anyone.

33:09.060 --> 33:12.060
Not until I know exactly what I'm dealing with.

33:12.060 --> 33:14.100
Well, er, take as much time as you need,

33:14.100 --> 33:17.060
but keep me abreast of developments.

33:28.740 --> 33:30.060
So, what do you think?

33:30.060 --> 33:33.260
She takes a good photo, Ellie.

33:33.260 --> 33:36.060
Sorry. That's not what you want to hear.

33:36.060 --> 33:39.100
She won't listen to me. I thought about confiscating her laptop,

33:39.100 --> 33:42.060
- but then she'd still have a phone.
- Well, take that, too.

33:42.060 --> 33:44.060
But then I've got no way of getting hold of her, have I?

33:44.060 --> 33:45.060
Oh, God.

33:45.060 --> 33:47.580
It's not easy being a single parent, is it?

33:47.580 --> 33:50.060
- You can't do good cop, bad cop.
- But I do bad cop pretty well.

33:50.060 --> 33:51.060
Hm.

33:54.060 --> 33:56.060
Jeez, Karen, it's tricky. I don't know what to suggest.

33:56.060 --> 33:57.100
No, Jen didn't either.

33:57.100 --> 34:00.060
So, come on, then. How's your therapy going?

34:00.060 --> 34:02.060
Ah!

34:02.060 --> 34:03.900
Ah-ha, it's brilliant.

34:03.900 --> 34:05.060
I'm a changed man.

34:05.060 --> 34:07.060
Unrecognisable.

34:08.060 --> 34:10.060
Hey...

34:10.060 --> 34:13.060
Maybe this will, erm, sort itself out.

34:13.060 --> 34:15.060
God, I hope so.

34:15.060 --> 34:17.060
Yeah.

34:17.060 --> 34:19.060
OK, when the water boils, that's when you add the pasta.

34:19.060 --> 34:21.060
Why do I need to know this? I'm 14.

34:21.060 --> 34:23.060
I should be watching YouTube.

34:23.060 --> 34:25.060
Cos you need to learn some independence.

34:25.060 --> 34:28.060
You can't rely on me always being there to do it for you.

34:28.060 --> 34:29.900
Why? Have you got other plans, love?

34:31.260 --> 34:33.060
Iron the sleeves first, OK?

34:33.060 --> 34:35.060
- I'm home.
- Collar and sleeves.

34:35.060 --> 34:37.060
Dad! Save us!

34:37.060 --> 34:39.100
Mum's trying to teach us life skills.

34:41.060 --> 34:43.060
Are you all right, son?

34:43.060 --> 34:46.060
Adam, please, hello. You're meant to be watching this.

34:46.060 --> 34:49.060
- You might be in digs next year.
- I'll just eat Pot Noodles.

34:49.060 --> 34:50.580
That got me through uni.

34:50.580 --> 34:52.100
Yeah, One-Pot Pete.

34:52.100 --> 34:54.060
- Oh, shit.
- What?

34:54.060 --> 34:57.060
It's an e-mail from the festival.

34:57.060 --> 34:59.060
- Well, go on, open it!
- I can't.

34:59.060 --> 35:01.060
Oh, give it here.

35:02.420 --> 35:04.060
Well?

35:06.060 --> 35:08.060
You got in!

35:08.060 --> 35:09.060
Aw...!

35:09.060 --> 35:11.060
Oh, brilliant!

35:14.060 --> 35:16.060
What's Teed Off?

35:16.060 --> 35:19.060
- Huh?
- You spent, erm, £48 there.

35:19.060 --> 35:21.060
They sell golfing equipment.

35:21.060 --> 35:24.060
- Are you checking up on me?
- No, I'm just checking for fraud.

35:24.060 --> 35:26.060
- Balls.
- Don't you do that?

35:26.060 --> 35:28.060
Hm? No, I meant golf balls.

35:28.060 --> 35:31.060
- That's what I bought.  -
- Oh. They're expensive, aren't they?

35:31.060 --> 35:33.060
- Don't lose them.
- Lose my balls...

35:33.060 --> 35:34.580
I already have.

35:36.060 --> 35:38.060
- Nikki?
- Yeah?

35:38.060 --> 35:39.060
I hate to say this, but...

35:39.060 --> 35:42.060
Urgh, your struggling with not being the bread-winner.

35:42.060 --> 35:44.420
I'm sorry. Sorry, go on.

35:44.420 --> 35:48.060
I know you don't like me getting cash out with your credit card,

35:48.060 --> 35:51.060
but...I'm running a bit low.

35:51.060 --> 35:53.060
Just take some out of my purse.

36:01.740 --> 36:04.060
You won't spend it all on sweets, will you, David?

36:04.060 --> 36:06.060
No, I won't. Thank you, Nikki.

36:08.060 --> 36:11.420
Oh, God...

36:15.060 --> 36:17.260
A big break for the lad, eh, this festival?

36:17.260 --> 36:20.060
No, thanks to you they got in.

36:21.060 --> 36:23.060
Our Adam said you missed the audition.

36:23.060 --> 36:25.740
Lucky Ian could take them.

36:25.740 --> 36:27.900
- Ian?
- My tutor. You know that.

36:27.900 --> 36:29.060
Where were you anyway?

36:30.060 --> 36:32.060
Oh, you weren't with that Evan?

36:32.060 --> 36:33.420
Pete, for goodness' sakes.

36:33.420 --> 36:35.420
Well, they got in, didn't they?

36:35.420 --> 36:37.580
It feels like you spend more time with him

36:37.580 --> 36:39.740
- than you do with us at the minute.
- He needs me, Jen.

36:39.740 --> 36:42.420
- What about his family?
- He hasn't got one.

36:42.420 --> 36:44.060
Yeah, well, you do.

36:46.060 --> 36:49.060
And they're going to need you more than ever, Pete.

36:49.060 --> 36:50.060
Why?

36:54.060 --> 36:57.060
I don't know. Kids, they're at that stage, aren't they?

36:57.060 --> 36:58.060
Look...

36:59.060 --> 37:04.060
I know you mean well, Pete, but you're not doing Evan any favours.

37:04.060 --> 37:05.740
The more he uses you as a crutch,

37:05.740 --> 37:08.060
the more he'll come to depend on you.

37:09.060 --> 37:11.060
That's not fair on anyone.

37:12.580 --> 37:14.060
Hm?

37:26.060 --> 37:29.100
Hello, Rex. You're a first-time caller, I believe?

37:29.100 --> 37:31.260
Uh, yes. A virgin, you might say.

37:31.260 --> 37:33.060
Well, welcome to my world.

37:33.060 --> 37:36.060
Do you want to turn your webcam on?

37:36.060 --> 37:38.740
- I'm a little shy.
- Don't be.

37:38.740 --> 37:40.900
We're all friends here.

37:40.900 --> 37:43.060
That's better.

37:44.060 --> 37:45.900
- Adam!
- Hi, Ellie.

37:45.900 --> 37:48.060
Rex is my online name.

37:48.060 --> 37:51.060
So, how does this thing work? Should I start?

37:51.060 --> 37:53.100
Those photos on your home page are lovely.

37:53.100 --> 37:56.060
- Adam, this is weird.
- Why?

37:56.060 --> 37:58.060
- Because I know you.
- Oh, yeah, you're right.

37:59.740 --> 38:03.060
So, isn't it weirder if you don't know the person?

38:03.060 --> 38:05.060
Did my mum put you up to this?

38:05.060 --> 38:08.060
No, she doesn't know. She might think it's a bit creepy.

38:08.060 --> 38:09.060
It is!

38:09.060 --> 38:12.060
Yeah. The whole thing is, Ellie, all of it.

38:12.060 --> 38:15.060
Some sad-sack in Stoke can't get a date,

38:15.060 --> 38:17.060
so he resorts to befriending hot chicks online.

38:17.060 --> 38:20.060
- Adam.
- And don't pretend there isn't a sexual element to it.

38:20.060 --> 38:22.260
I mean, not for you, but...

38:22.260 --> 38:25.580
Ellie, what do you think the first thing these guys do

38:25.580 --> 38:27.060
when they log off?

38:28.900 --> 38:31.060
Exactly. You're better than that, Ellie.

38:31.060 --> 38:33.060
You know, you're smart.

38:33.060 --> 38:37.060
It's not an inappropriate thing for me to say, you're beautiful.

38:37.060 --> 38:39.060
Don't sell yourself short.

38:39.060 --> 38:42.060
Don't sell yourself at all.

38:45.060 --> 38:46.740
OK.

38:46.740 --> 38:48.260
Hey, I'll see you at your birthday, eh?

38:48.260 --> 38:50.060
Oh...

38:50.060 --> 38:51.580
What would you like as a present?

39:02.060 --> 39:04.420
- I thought you said I could call you any time.
- Well, I did.

39:04.420 --> 39:07.060
I just didn't think it'd be so often.

39:07.060 --> 39:09.260
Oh, so, "I'll always be there for you, Evan"

39:09.260 --> 39:12.060
actually means between six and eight on alternate Wednesdays.

39:12.060 --> 39:15.060
Well, I take my daughter to dance on Wednesdays.

39:16.060 --> 39:18.740
Look, you're doing really well. Your medication's kicking in.

39:18.740 --> 39:20.060
You don't need me.

39:21.060 --> 39:24.060
- Are you breaking up with me?
- It's not like that.

39:25.060 --> 39:27.060
It feels like that.

39:27.060 --> 39:30.060
Like when me dad walked out, the same rejection.

39:30.060 --> 39:32.060
Look, Evan, please.

39:32.060 --> 39:34.060
Well, there are other people out there

39:34.060 --> 39:36.420
who can help you better than me.

39:36.420 --> 39:39.060
Your doctor, old friends,

39:39.060 --> 39:41.260
the Samaritans.

39:41.260 --> 39:43.580
I can't do this.

39:45.060 --> 39:47.060
I'm sorry, I've got to go.

39:49.060 --> 39:52.060
Right, well, if I kill myself, it'll be on you!

